From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Override hardware concurrency and device memory at system level

Detection vector: navigator.hardwareConcurrency and navigator.deviceMemory
expose the machine's CPU core count and RAM. Combined with other signals
they contribute to unique device identification. In headless VMs these
values often differ from real consumer machines.

This patch allows these values to be set via command line flags.

Surface: system
Closes: hasHighHardwareConcurrency, hardware fingerprinting

--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ unsigned Navigator::hardwareConcurrency() const {
+  // AgenticBrowser: override with --ab-cores=N if set.
+  if (ab_hardware_concurrency_ > 0) return ab_hardware_concurrency_;

@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ unsigned Navigator::deviceMemory() const {
+  // AgenticBrowser: override with --ab-memory=N if set.
+  if (ab_device_memory_ > 0) return ab_device_memory_;
